						h3.ar-tutheading.wf-bg.f-oku.wtxt.curve.text-center EXAMPLE 1
						p.ar-text In this example, we're going to use Wayfarer's Tremors card to make use of Courage From Beyond. You can follow along below or check out an animated tutorial by using the button controls!
						br
						col-md-12.ar-cardpanel
							img.ar-himg.center-block(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/a_270,e_auto_contrast,q_54:420,r_25/v1498676135/tremors.jpg")
							h3.ar-cardheading.wf-bg.f-adv.wtxt tremors		
						br
						p.ar-text Tremors is a Feat card available in Wayfarer's deck. Played by itself, Tremors allows you to reverb - swapping your deck and discard pile in the process. Wayfarer begins the game with 12 cards in his deck and it only gets more dangerous from there. Tremors acts like a hall pass - giving you at least one way to reset you life total. Let's get it started - let's choose to active Tremors this turn in order to swap our deck and our discard pile.  
						
						br
						p.ar-text Here comes the hard part. When you Reverb, it's a two-part process. First, you must trash the first three cards of your discard pile. Trashed cards are considered outside of the game - neither in your deck, discard pile or hand. Nine times out of ten, that means you can't expect to see those cards again in this game. 
						br
						p.ar-text After trashing the top three cards of your discard pile, you then exchange your deck and your discard pile. Sometimes it's better to hold off on your Reverb triggers until your life has reached a low total - for instance, using Reverb on turn 1 would leave you with twelve cards in both your deck and your discard pile. 
						br
						.col-md-12.ar-cardpanel
							img.ar-vimg.center-block(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/e_auto_contrast,q_54:420,r_25/v1498676135/couragefrombeyond.jpg")
							h3.ar-cardheading.wf-bg.f-adv.wtxt courage from beyond
						br
						p.ar-text So if Reverb is purely defensive, how does Wayfarer win against the aggressive earthlings? Courage From Beyond gives us a clue - by trashing large portions of his deck, Wayfarer can boost his incredible alien abilities if left alone. Courage From Beyond grants you a free turn, but Wayfarer has many ways to take advantage of his trashed cards.
